caption.paragraph:
TABLE 2. Morphometric (in mm) and meristic data for
HyPogeoPhis Pti
sp. nov. All specimens are in the BMNH collection. AG_vent = incomplete AGs interrupted by vent and disc;

subSubSection.paragraph:
Small terminal cap, slightly longer than three quarters length of adjacent PAs. Posteriormost AG transversely narrow, restricted to dorsum, approximately level with back of disc surrounding vent. No AGs on venter behind centre of the vent. Terminus bluntly rounded, much more so than head; inconspicuous terminal ‘keel’ visible as pale narrow line from behind disc onto posteroventral surface of TT. Disc not well circumscribed, subcircular (diameter ca. 
1.2 mm
), very slightly depressed, with nine (four posterior, two lateral, three anterior) fairly bilaterally symmetrical denticulations, those lateral and posterior longest, those posteromedial much the largest; vent circular to slightly transverse, somewhat V-shaped.
